messages:
Name: Tammy Abraham
Nationality: England
Date of Birth: October 2, 1997
Position: Attacker
Current club: Milan
Serie A clubs played for: Roma, Milan

Milan's Tammy Abraham has made 29 appearances in this season's Serie A, with 28 of these coming for his current club. He had previously played for Roma in the competition during 2024/2025, appearing one time.

Abraham last made an appearance in a competition game on April 27, playing 64 minutes for Milan versus Venezia in a 2-0 victory. The attacker has netted three Serie A goals this season. He has been shown one yellow card.
It was versus Fiorentina on April 5 when Abraham last scored, netting in a 2-2 draw. His opening goal of the campaign came in the 4-0 victory against Venezia on September 14.
Last season for Roma, Abraham made eight Serie A appearances and scored one goal.

Abraham moved to Milan on loan in August 2024 from Roma, for whom he has made 84 league appearances in total, scoring 26 goals and providing seven assists, after joining the club in August 2021 from Chelsea.

Abraham made his first Serie A appearance for Roma on August 22, 2021, playing 69 minutes as a starter versus Fiorentina at the age of 23 years and 324 days. He first appeared in a Serie A fixture for current club Milan in the encounter versus Lazio on August 31, 2024.

So far in his Serie A career, he has appeared in 112 games in the competition, with 29 goals and 11 assists. Despite appearing 112 times so far, Abraham is yet to be sent off in the competition, with 13 yellow cards collected overall.
